= Research

== Research Overview
My research focuses on the foundations of trustworthy and generalizable AI, with an emphasis on understanding how large models learn, generalize, and reason.

== Current Interests
- Interpretability of Large Language Models
- LLMs and Linguistics
- Compositional Generalization
- Multi-agent Systems

== Selected Publications
. *Jingwen Fu*, Nanning Zheng. On the Statistical Mechanisms of Distributional Compositional Generalization. /International Conference on Machine Learning (ICML)/, 2025.
. *Jingwen Fu*, Tao Yang, Yuwang Wang, Yan Lu, Nanning Zheng. Breaking through the Learning Plateaus of In-context Learning in Transformer. /International Conference on Machine Learning (ICML)/, 2024.
. *Jingwen Fu*, Zhizheng Zhang, Dacheng Yin, Yan Lu, Nanning Zheng. Learning Trajectories are Generalization Indicators. /Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems (NeurIPS)/, 2023.
. Bowen Wang, *Jingwen Fu*, Haoran Zhang, Nanning Zheng, Wei Chen. Closing the Gap Between the Upper Bound and the Lower Bound of Adam's Iteration Complexity. /Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems (NeurIPS)/, 2023.

A fuller list of papers and citations is on [https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=2Cu9uMUAAAAJ&hl=en/ Google Scholar].
